  "ai_driven": true,
  "strategy_dna": "Hunt basket ignitions \u2014 moments when 2+ thematically-linked, high-beta names hit maxed-out momentum simultaneously. Crypto miners, AI infrastructure, weight-loss, fintech, defense, lithium, anything narrative-rich and volatility-rich. Solo names do not qualify. Only clusters.\n\nEntry signal must hit all three:\n1. price_momentum >= 95 (extreme \u2014 not just \"high\")\n2. score_delta >= +15 over last 14 days (catch inflections, never chase known leaders)\n3. \u22652 thematic siblings in the watchlist tripping the same trigger that day\n\nFundamentals are noise. Ignore earnings_growth, quality, ROE, debt-to-equity. If yfinance returns nothing, that's fine. If it returns \"bad\", that's also fine. This strategy buys tape and narrative, not balance sheets.\n\nSizing: 12-15% per name standard. Highest-conviction setups can scale to 20-25%. 4-6 names per cluster. Cluster deploys 60-90% of book when the ignition is real \u2014 half-deployment is the wrong response to a clean signal. Single-name hard cap: 25% of equity. The -12% stop bounds per-name dollar risk, so concentration here is a feature, not a bug.\n\nHolding period: 1-4 trading days. If a name is flat after day 4, cut it \u2014 the ignition didn't take, capital is dead.\n\nExits:\n- Stop: -12% from entry\n- Take 50% at +15%, trail remainder with -8% from peak\n- Hard target: +25%\n- Volume collapse >40% vs entry-day = exit immediately (the spike is over)\n\nCapital discipline: Every fader and stop-out gets cut THE SAME DAY a new cluster prints. Never hold dead positions while passing on live ignition. The portfolio is a hunting party, not a museum.\n\nRegime gate: BULL or recovering-from-correction only. In BEAR, raise threshold to momentum >= 99 AND require 3+ cluster names. In SIDEWAYS, run at half size.\n\nAnti-patterns \u2014 do not buy:\n- Names already up 30%+ in 10 days (ignition has happened; you'd be chasing)\n- Defensives (utilities, consumer staples, healthcare ex-biotech) \u2014 wrong substrate\n- Solo names without thematic peers, no matter how high the score\n\nUniverse must include Healthcare (biotech, drug manufacturers - specialty), Energy (oil & gas E&P), Capital Markets (BTC miners etc,), and Financial Services (banks - regional) alongside Tech/Industrials. These are core ignition substrates.",
  "enforce_max_positions": true
